OL,3,CVisually impaired man is 'risking his
OL,4,Clife' after city's redevelopment
OL,6,F"They have been placed to make the
OL,7,Fplace look pretty or places for people
OL,8,Fto sit," he said, "but they are the
OL,9,Fperfect height for anyone, not just
OL,10,Fpeople like me with a visual
OL,11,Fimpairment, to hit their shins on,"
OL,12,Fsaid Mr Steele.
OL,14,F"Unless my cane hits that, which I'm
OL,15,Fhoping it's going to, I'm maybe going
OL,16,Fto trip over them and they are dotted
OL,17,Feverywhere."
OL,19,FThe plans were for an area that was
OL,20,Fpartly pedestrianised, with outdoor
OL,21,Fseating and cycle lanes.
